tool.name: condition_darkTargets

param.name: year_workspace
param.dialogReference: Select the folder containing the raw files for the desired year's imagery.For example, selecting the "2010" folder in the "Products" directory will process all the dark targets shapefiles for 2010.

param.name: attrEvalSQL
param.dialogReference:
This is the evaluation criteria applied to select one set of attribute values in those regions of overlapping dark targets containing two sets of attributes.This expression is in SQLformat.

Attribute field names from the first set of attributes maintain the same names (such as "PcontrDB"), while attribute field names from the second set of attributes have a "_1" suffix appended to them (such as "PcontrDB_1").

This evaluation criteria should compare values from equivalent fields (for example, both "PcontrDB" fields) in order to choose which set of attribute values should be applied to the overlapping polygon.

tool.summary:
This script imports all the dark targets shapefiles within a selected year that are produced by the target detection process on RADARSAT-2 imagery.

The data is cleaned up and same day acquisitions are merged together into a single feature class per day.

The data is conditioned and organized in a file geodatabase that is created with the same name and located in the same directory as the selected folder. If the file geodatabase already exists,this script will overwrite it!
tool.usage: This script is used to convert the dark targets shapefiles into conditioned feature classes that are ready for subsequent analysis. Select the folder which contains the desired year's shapefiles and the process will produce a file geodatabase containing the conditioned data for that year.
